<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-04-23T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-04-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="478" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d478">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00Sonora/781: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Nogales</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Damm</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nogales, Ariz</hi></placeName>., <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-23T18:00:00-06:00">April 23, 1929—6
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:37 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>From Guaymas.</p>
                        <p>“Urgent. April 23, 4 p.m. Please expedite reply my April 22, 1 p.m., as
                            similar case arises in connection with Standard Oil Company stocks at
                            Yavaros, and it may become necessary to request to have ordered to
                            Yavaros destroyer <hi rend="italic">Selfridge</hi> now on the way to
                            relieve <hi rend="italic">Robert Smith</hi> at Guaymas.”</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Damm</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>